61.5	The_Trial	The Trial	The Trial (Kafka's original German title: , later as and ) is a novel by Franz Kafka, first published in 1925. One of Kafka's best-known works, it tells the story of a man arrested and prosecuted by a remote, inaccessible authority, with the nature of his crime revealed neither to him nor the reader.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/87/Kafka_Der_Prozess_1925.jpg/200px-Kafka_Der_Prozess_1925.jpg
